sity+Press&amp;rft.date=1970&amp;rft.aulast=Grousset.&amp;rft.aufirst=Ren%C3%A9&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AStone+Tower+%28Ptolemy%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Stein, Aurel (1928). <i>Innermost Asia: Detailed Report of Explorations in Central Asia, Kansu, and Eastern \u012ar\u0101n Carried Out and Described under the Orders of H.M. Indian Government (4 Volumes.)</i>. Oxford: Clarendon Press. pp.&#160;847\u201351 (Vol 2).</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Innermost+Asia%3A+Detailed+Report+of+Explorations+in+Central+Asia%2C+Kansu%2C+and+Eastern+%C4%AAr%C4%81n+Carried+Out+and+Described+under+the+Orders+of+H.M.+Indian+Government+%284+Volumes.%29&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rft.pages=847-51+%28Vol+2%29&amp;rft.pub=Clarendon+Press&amp;rft.date=1928&amp;rft.aulast=Stein&amp;rft.aufirst=Aurel&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AStone+Tower+%28Ptolemy%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Stein, Aurel (1933). <i>On Ancient Central-Asian Tracks</i>. London: MacMillian. p.&#160;295.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=On+Ancient+Central-Asian+Tracks&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pages=295&amp;rft.pub=MacMillian&amp;rft.date=1933&amp;rft.aulast=Stein&amp;rft.aufirst=Aurel&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AStone+Tower+%28Ptolemy%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-:2-10\"><span class=